OPEN SOURCE

This page sets out the details of the licences that apply to the open source 
software used in NewsKit. You should read and comply with the terms of these 
licences when using NewsKit.


NEWS UK SOFTWARE

The code that has been developed by or on behalf of News UK to form the basis 
of NewsKit (“NewsKit OSS”) is published by News UK under the 3-Clause BSD License. 
The terms of the 3-Clause BSD License are shown below.


THIRD PARTY SOFTWARE

NewsKit incorporates some components of open source software published by people 
other than News UK.  Details of these components, and their related licences, 
are set out in the table below.

The NewsKit OSS also refers, or links, to other components of open source software 
published by people other than News UK. You should ensure that you check, 
and comply with, the terms of the licences for those components before using them.

There may be provisions in the licences for these third party components or NewsKit 
OSS that override aspects of News UK’s Website Terms and Conditions.


